    <narrative xml:lang="EN">SWAp arrangement agreed between the Government of Ghana and Development Partners and operationalized.</narrative>
   </title>
   <reference code="264314" vocabulary="99"></reference>
   <indicator aggregation-status="0" ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2015 discussions commenced between the Government of Ghana and development partners on the feasibility of a Sector Wide Approach modality to support decentralization together with the possibility of an EU joint programming for the sector. In order to improve upon the relevance, efficiency and effectiveness of development assistance in the sector the SWAp was agreed. The SWAp would require DPs to channel their resources under government leadership to implement an approved sector policy and adopt a common approach aimed at achieving the objectives of decentralization in Ghana</narrative>
